                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Thanks for all the advice, I sold my FT2 belt and bought the ID4 belt. I am liking it much better. Personally, it depends on the camp I am at. I tested my mana without the FT2 belt before I sold it and I was able to clear all 8 guardians in HoH and still have around 30 - 50% mana depending on spells being resisted. Without the belt I still have FT4 and no points in mental clarity so I think in the long run the ID4 belt will be much better for me. Also, with the sale of the FT2 belt I was able to buy myself an Ornate silk turban pattern which frees me up from casting a vision spell and opens a buff slot. So all in all I think I made the correct choice.</span id="msg"></font></td>
